What is usability testing in UX?\par
Usability Testing: What It Is, Benefits, and What It Isn't\par
Usability testing is a method of testing the functionality of a website, app, or other digital product by observing real users as they attempt to complete tasks on it. The users are usually observed by researchers working for a business during either an in-person or, more commonly, a remote usability testing session.\f0\par
