Select a usability testing tool.\par
Set up the study.\par
Run a pilot test.\par
Recruit the participants.\par
Analyze the results.\par
\par
A pilot experiment, pilot study, pilot test or pilot project is a small-scale preliminary study\par
conducted to evaluate feasibility, duration, cost, adverse events, and improve upon the study design prior to performance of a full-scale research project.\par
A company has developed a new mobile app for booking flights. Before releasing the app to the public, they would conduct pilot tests by selecting a small group of users to test it in real-world scenarios\par
A pilot test is an initial test or a miniature version of a larger-scale study or project. \par
The term "pilot" means to test a plan, project, or other strategy before implementing it more fully across an organization.\par
A pilot test is generally conducted before beta testing in the case of a product or software release.\par
Pilot testing focuses on testing every single piece of your app, while user acceptance testing focuses on finding bugs and usability problems in the front end, or user side, of the app.\par
